column5: Cold and still last night. 9am today the Bay was flat and still with lots of mist rising off of it. We'll see what the next few weeks bring.
cooks bay is frozen up from lastnight.
I was talking to someone who looked out from the 8th line of Innisfil and he said there was a slim of ice on parts of cooks  bay
What are you waiting for??????? Wheres your underwater reports????????
was out on the ice this morning        notice: picture and video from other years..the ice is not safe
Now Now Terry.. dont' get them headin for the lake!!  But we CAN get to my dock by sled !!!!!
you mean there is good ice somewhere
Yep.. Doug.. broken leg and all.. is packing the road from town to his house and mine.
They are running sleds and 4 wheelers on Cooks Bay as of yesterday.
no, no no on the keswick side there is ice out about a 1/4 of a mile but it is just broken ice and slush that has blown in there not safe not even close
